Description: 5 fragments of pages of a Coptic codex. Twelve frames (EA 76565-76) are stored together in an archival box.
Curator's comments: Mounted in a frame with the label 'Unrolled Sept. 1848. No 1'. Typed labels stuck to the glass read: 'Miscellaneous fragments. Gift of Papyri from Hartwell House by Messrs. Rutter and Marchant. [Then in biro:] May 11th 1935'. The group of 12 frames (EA 76565-76) are stored togther in an archival box. EA 76415 may belong to the same group.
Previously unregistered material stored in Papyrus Store.
Acquisition notes: 'Gift of papyri from Hartwell House by Messrs Rutter and Marchant.'
